column1: The analyses tabulated here are for the 95 transcripts with differential expression by schizophrenia status from the study of the RUCDR-transformed LCLs (268 RUCDR cases and 446 RUCDR controls) using the 12 measured covariates, and restricted to transcripts detected in 80% or more subjects. To the right of the primary analysis (RUCDR-transformed LCLs using the 12 measured covariates), we also list the differential expression p-values, beta coefficients, and FDR for the Australia-transformed cases (145 Australia cases and 446 RUCDR controls) using the 12 measured covariates.  All FDR values were calculated based on the 14,588 transcripts detected in 80% or more subjects.  Immune-related, i.e., protein-coding gene function containing “immune” from genecards.org, is noted (yes, no, or NA for those unlisted).
